Complete NFT Metadata Specification v1.6.1-visionary-AI (including Optional, Platform-Specific, and Game-Related Features)
1. Schema Declaration:

$schema: "https://metadata.opensea.io/schema/v1.5.0-visionary"
version: "1.6.1-visionary-AI"
2. Base Standard Metadata (v1.1):

name: String (NFT name)
description: String (NFT description)
image: String (URL of main image)
external_url: String (Optional URL for external website)
attributes: Array of objects (list of traits)
trait_type: String (trait name)
value: String or Int (trait value)
display_type: String (Optional, display format like "number", "date", "percentage")
3. Experimental Enhancements (v1.2, v1.3, v1.4):

dynamic_content: Object (Optional)
external_data_sources: Array of Strings (URLs for real-time data feeds)
update_frequency: String (e.g., "hourly", "daily", "event-driven")
ai_variations_enabled: Boolean (whether AI generates visual variations)
ai_model_url: String (Optional, URL of AI model for variations)
interactive_elements: Array of objects (list of interactive elements)
type: String ("voice", "touch", "scan", "proximity", "gameplay")
trigger: String (specific trigger event for interaction)
responses: Array of Strings (Optional, for voice or text interactions)
gameplay_effect: String (Optional, effect on game mechanics)
4. Visionary Features (v1.5.0-visionary, v1.6.1 enhancements):

metaverse_integration: Object (Optional)
model_url: String (URL of 3D model for metaverse platforms)
supported_platforms: Array of Strings ("Decentraland", "Sandbox", etc.)
interactive_elements: Array of objects (like above, specific to metaverse)
real_world_linkages: Object (Optional)
physical_asset_id: String (ID of linked physical asset)
redemption_instructions: String (instructions for claiming physical asset)
on_chain_storage: Object (Optional)
storage_provider: String ("Arweave", "IPFS")
content_hash: String (hash of on-chain storage location)
platform_specific: Object (Optional)
[platform_name]: Object (specific data for each platform)
[platform-specific fields and values]
5. Game-Related Features (v1.6.1 additions):

stats: Array of objects (gameplay statistics)
stat_name: String (name of stat)
value: Int or Float (initial value of stat)
max_value: Int or Float (Optional, maximum achievable value)
abilities: Array of objects (special abilities)
ability_name: String (name of ability)
description: String (description of ability)
trigger: String (event or condition that activates the ability)
effect: String (description of ability's effect)
inventory: Array of objects (list of in-game items)
item_name: String (name of item)
description: String (item description)
image_url: String (Optional, URL of item image)
stats_modifier: Object (Optional, how item affects stats)
[stat_name]: Int or Float (amount added/subtracted)
6. Accessibility and Ethical Considerations (v1.6.0 additions):

accessibility_features: Object (Optional)
alt_text: String (description of visuals for screen readers)
transcript: String (Transcript of audio/visual content)
ethical_considerations: Object (Optional)
carbon_footprint: String (estimated carbon footprint)
artist_compensation: String (details of artist royalties/rights)
7. Additional Notes:

This specification is a suggested standard and can be adapted to specific project requirements
